<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-829-574  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 829 574.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IBM System User  August 1990 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Small sites with big problems. (smaller IBM computer sites investin continuous staff training)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sweet, Pat.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Smaller IBM computer sites begin to invest in ongoing DP stafftraining to retain employees, particularly in cases where theAS/400 has been recently installed.andP;  Training policies are gainingpopularity because the availability of staff with AS/400,System/36 or 38 experience is so low.andP;  For smaller sites, trainingmay tempt employees to take their supplemented skills to a larger,higher paying company, but more often an organization that breedsits own people may actually encourage company loyalty andcommitment to one's professional growth.andP;  Many staff appreciate acompany that clearly shows an interest in their career developmentby offering training courses and subsequent financial reward.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM AS/400 (Minicomputer) (user education).andO;Topic:     Training of EmployeesEmploymentComputer Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>